Project Summary
===============
Futuristische Digitale Klok — een cyberpunk-stijl real-time klok op een donker scherm. Neon cyan cijfers met glow-effecten, scanlines overlay, digit flip animaties, progressiebalk voor seconden en floating particles. Full-viewport display zonder interactie. Gebaseerd op het design spec uit `.walden-memories/design-spec.md`.

Architecture Overview
====================
Single-page Next.js App Router app. Server Components by default; any interactivity lives in client components under `components/`. Top-level routing files (`page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `not-found.tsx`, `error.tsx`, `loading.tsx`) are all server components — `'use client'` NEVER appears at this level (breaks WebContainer prerendering). Styling is Tailwind CSS 4 via `@import "tailwindcss";` in `app/globals.css`.

Key Components
==============

- **Page** (`app/page.tsx`) — Server Component wrapper. Imports and renders `<DigitalClock />`.
- **DigitalClock** (`components/DigitalClock.tsx`) — Hoofd client component. Laadt JetBrains Mono, gebruikt `useTime`, coördineert alle sub-componenten, handelt minuut/uur-flash af.
- **BackgroundLayer** (`components/clock/BackgroundLayer.tsx`) — Animated radial gradients + floating particles. Client component.
- **ScanlineOverlay** (`components/clock/ScanlineOverlay.tsx`) — Fixed scanlines overlay. Server component.
- **ClockDigit** (`components/clock/ClockDigit.tsx`) — Individueel cijfer met digit-in flip animatie via React key. Client component.
- **ClockColon** (`components/clock/ClockColon.tsx`) — Pulserende dubbele punt met colon-pulse animatie.
- **DateDisplay** (`components/clock/DateDisplay.tsx`) — Nederlandse datumopmaak met groeiende decoratielijnen.
- **SecondsBar** (`components/clock/SecondsBar.tsx`) — Horizontale progressiebalk (0→60s) met cyan glow. Client component.
- **useTime** (`hooks/useTime.ts`) — Custom hook: `useState<Date>` + `setInterval(1000)`. Initialiseert op `null` (SSR-safe), update elke seconde.
- **RootLayout** (`app/layout.tsx`) — Root HTML shell. Loads Geist Sans + Geist Mono via `next/font/google` and defines SEO metadata. Antialiasing enabled.
- **Error Boundary** (`app/error.tsx`) — Runtime error recovery with retry.
- **NotFound** (`app/not-found.tsx`) — 404 page. Plain server component using only `Link` from `next/link` and inline SVG.
- **Loading** (`app/loading.tsx`) — Route transition spinner.

Agent Memory
============
- `.walden-memories/` — shared folder where specialists write working documents for each other. Design specs, debug reports, SEO audits. Agents read from here instead of receiving large specs through Walden's token budget.

Invariants
==========
- `app/*/page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `not-found.tsx`, `error.tsx` are ALWAYS Server Components. No `'use client'`, no hooks, no event handlers at this layer.
- Client interactivity (useState, useEffect, onClick) lives in `components/*.tsx` with `'use client'`.
- No database. No env vars. No auth. No persistence — any state is ephemeral.
- `.env.local` exists at project root but is managed by the app (not written by agents directly).

Notes for agents
================
- Dependencies, versions, and the directory tree are NOT duplicated here. Read `package.json` or `list_directory` for that.
- When you change the project structure, update THIS file accordingly: add new components under Key Components, document new invariants, update the Architecture Overview if the fundamental shape shifts.
